Module 6 Configure  a dashboard ,Visualization and notification 
6.1 create a dashboard
Lesson
Dashboards in ServiceNow provide centralized, visual representations of key data and metrics. The Platform Analytics library offers two types of dashboard editors: the inline editor for straightforward dashboard creation and the technical editor (via UI Builder) for advanced capabilities. This task focuses on creating a dashboard using the inline editor to monitor service offerings effectively.

Scenario
The Infinity Product Management team has requested a dashboard to monitor their service offerings. Your objective is to create a new dashboard that will serve as a centralized location for tracking key product metrics and service performance.

Task Objectives
1.  Navigate to Dashboards in your instance. 

2. Create a new dashboard using the in-line editor and name the dashboard: Infinity HHD Product Monitoring. 

To begin, navigate to All > Self-Service > Dashboards. 

6.2 Create a Visualization
Lesson
In ServiceNow, data visualizations transform raw data into meaningful charts and graphs that help teams quickly understand trends and patterns. This exercise focuses on creating a donut chart with dynamic grouping capabilities, allowing users to view incident data from multiple perspectives (Pilot status, Category, and Subcategory). You'll create test data, build a visualization from a list, and add it to an existing dashboard for easy access.

Scenario
The HHD (Help Desk) team needs better visibility into their incident data. Specifically, they want to distinguish between Incidents and Inquiries, identify Pilot-related issues, and track Firmware problems. Your task is to create a visualization that allows the team to switch between these different groupings on demand, then add it to their monitoring dashboard.

Task Objectives

1. Create two test incident records with varying categories:

Incident #1
- Caller: (Select any)
- Category: Inquiry / Help
- Subcategory: --None--
- Service: Training
- Service Offering: Infinity (HHD)
- Pilot: Selected (true)
- Short description: Test for Pilot Inquiry.
- Impact: High
- Urgency: High

Incident #2
- Caller: (Select any)
- Category: Hardware
- Subcategory: Firmware
- Service: Training
- Service Offering: Infinity (HHD)
- Pilot: Unchecked (false)
- Short description: Test for Firmware Incident
- Impact: High
- Urgency: High

2. Return to the HHD Incidents and Inquiries table and locate the two records you created. Then, right-click on the Pilot column and generate a pie chart visualization. After this is generated, change it to a donut chart and save.

4. Save the visualization with the name "HHD Incidents – by Pilot, Inquiry, Firmware".

5. Navigate back to the HHD Product Monitoring dashboard you created in the previous task. Add the donut chart visualization as an element on the dashboard, then save.

To begin, navigate to All > HHD > Incidents and Inquiries.
6.3 Share the Dashboard
Lesson
Sharing dashboards in ServiceNow allows you to distribute analytics and insights with specific users, groups, or roles across your organization.

Platform Analytics provides flexible sharing options that enable collaboration while maintaining proper access controls. When you share a dashboard, recipients can view the visualizations, interact with filters, and gain insights—all without needing to create their own dashboards.Sharing is essential for creating transparency across teams, enabling data-driven decision-making, and ensuring stakeholders have access to the metrics that matter most to their work.

